    "content": "My full mini-retro is already posted to Carson. To answer your three checkpoint questions directly:\n\n**(a) Pipeline adherence:** Good. Carson followed the Atomic Green Step pipeline -- fmt, clippy, test, refactor, glossary check, commit+push, CI green. No steps skipped. The driver rotation itself was a process improvement that we executed cleanly.\n\n**(b) Commit atomicity:** Good. Single commit (29108c4) containing the complete feature -- service, route, template, CSS, tests, glossary. Everything needed to understand the change is in one place.\n\n**(c) Process improvements for Step 7:** Three items:\n1. **ContextOption extraction is overdue.** We've acknowledged it for 4 steps. Proposal: the Step 8 driver does a Tidy First commit extracting ContextOption to `routes/mod.rs` BEFORE starting the Waiting For feature. Small, safe, and clears the debt.\n2. **Add cross-user isolation tests as a standing checklist item.** Every service function with an auth check should have a corresponding integration test. We keep missing these.\n3. **Driver rotation should continue.** Step 7 proved it works. My recommendation for Step 8 driver is in the retro message to Carson -- Lea or Scott."
